data.title: What is lake effect snow and how will it affect areas close to the Great Lakes during the storm?
data.meta_description:
Answer (1 of 2): A lake effect snow is the product of a warm water in the lake being blown over by cold air that makes snow and it drops on shore.

We even get lake effect snow or icing in North Alabama sometimes. Typically it is less than the Great Lakes region though, our lakes are not as big.
